rewards.textDesc:
A page from a poetry anthology in Taran.
The poem will be all too familiar to most Victorians, as it is often required reading at secondary school.

A written invitation from Count Philip.
Possibly due to changes in the date and venue, this invitation is void by now.

A transport permit acquired by Heidi through due means.
It comes with a full page of restrictive terms.

A photo of a soldier, 'Bill.'
Seeing his picture now prompts the Self-Salvation Corps to look away with mixed feelings.

A black feather.
The black fowlbeasts have flown for the storm.

unlockData.initialDes: A book of personal notes discovered among our materials. Unclear which Londinier lost it, and uncertain if they are still alive. Tells of much that is happening in the city at the moment. Can be perused in the intervals between battle.
unlockData.finalDes: A notebook Heidi sought to pass to Rhodes Island mere days before being arrested, now returned to its rightful owner. Much that has happened in this city is recorded in a terse, obfuscated style. Heidi is more than glad to let you borrow it to peruse as often as you like.
unlockData.remindDes: While perusing the notes, you found an ID card, and on it a familiar name. Based on the handwriting both preceding and following, you can be sure she was the owner of the notebook.

rewards.textDesc:
A lookout tower standing tall in front of the Palace.
Being from several centuries ago, the tower has long since crumbled, leaving only a sketch to provide posterity a notion of what it originally looked like.

The identifying badge of the Captain of the Watch, who leads the Knights of the Tower.
An honor, and doubly so a responsibility.

The highest military award issued by Victoria.
Only found in the possession of truly heroic Victorian soldiers. You'll find more than one hanging in the White Wolf family hall, to boot.

A newspaper clipping filled with jubilation.
That day, all of Victoria's papers sang praises of Frederick III and his feat of conquering Gaul.

A clipping of the Palace amidst firelight.
No one knows where Victoria is headed.

unlockData.initialDes:
The Book of the Tower Knights, chronicling centuries of life for the Knights of the Tower.
Lent to you by Dagda for your perusal, serving as a window into Victoria's history.
